    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add the <strong>remaining berbere seasoning </strong>and <strong>tomato paste</strong> to the pan with your <strong>ginger & garlic paste</strong>, 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>and a small pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1671537094944-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1671537094944-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1671537094944-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1671537094944-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1671537094944-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> in 400ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[575ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [750ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Once fragrant, return the <strong>browned chicken </strong>to the pan, add the <strong>chicken stock </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat, then reboil a kettle</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook, covered, for 15-20 min or until the potato is fork-tender and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!)– this is your <strong>Ethiopian-style doro wat</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1671537099692-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1671537099692-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1671537099692-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1671537099692-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1671537099692-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>egg[s]</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a small pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat (salt prevents the eggs from cracking)</p><p>Once boiling, cook for exactly 8 min for perfect, mid-boiled eggs, then fill a bowl of very cold water and add the<strong> soft-boiled egg[s]</strong> to the bowl</p><p>Set aside, then once cooled, peel the <strong>cooled soft-boiled egg[s] </strong>and cut them in half</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1671537105352-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1671537105352-x400.jpg",
